e of the two components, as\nwell as the red excess emission via a slight ${\\rm{^{56}Ni}}$ enrichment in the\nouter $\\sim$ 0.5\\% of the ejecta mass. Our spectrum from 300 days post-peak\nadvances the constraint against non-degenerate companions and further supports\na near-Chandrasekhar-mass explosion origin. Off-center ignited\ndelayed-detonations of Chandrasekhar-mass white dwarfs may be responsible for\nthe observed features of SN 2021aefx in some normal Type Ia SNe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 2 Apr 2023 20:51:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Apr 2023 16:45:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-06"}
