ation of the in-plane thermal Hall effect in the\nspin-disordered state of alpha-RuCl3. For an accurate measurement of the\nthermal Hall effect, it is necessary to avoid crystals with the merohedral\ntwins contributing oppositely to k_xy, while the out-of-plane transport may\nhave a negligible effect. To deal with the field-induced rotational-symmetry\nbreaking, we propose two symmetry-based protocols, improved single-device and\ntwo-device methods.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Apr 2023 08:19:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-01"}
